column1: #Text=Aquinnah ( formerly known as Gay Head ) is a town at the western end of Martha 's Vineyard .
#Text=The bright , multi-colored clay cliffs at Gay Head are a fabulous sight .
#Text=Aquinnah is home to the Wampanoag Tribe , residents of Martha 's Vineyard for thousands of years and the majority population of the town .
#Text=The town consists of sparsely developed bluffs surrounded by beaches .
#Text=West Basin Bike Ferry , West Basin Road , Aquinnah .
#Text=Carries bicycles and people , but not cars , between Menemsha and the Lobsterville part of Aquinnah .
#Text=The #5 bus runs from West Tisbury through Chilmark to Gay Head , then loops along Lobsterville Road and back to Chilmark .
#Text=Bicycling is popular , but the roads are windy and steep .
#Text=The MTA bus provides limited service within Aquinnah .
#Text=Public area adjacent to the lighthouse with spectacular views of the beach below , Vineyard Sound , and Cuttyhunk
#Text=Tours on summer evenings to see the sunset $ 5 adults , under 12 free .
#Text=located on Moshup Trail just south of State Road , with beach access and a drop off spot located about 0.5 miles south of the pay lot .
#Text=This beach stretches for over a mile along the southwestern end of the island , wrapping around the Gay Head Light .
#Text=This beach is known for the picturesque clay cliffs that rise up from the edge of the beach .
#Text=Nudity is common and tolerated on the northern end of the beach .
#Text=Aquinnah police strictly enforce the ban on disturbing the clay cliffs , but do not enforce clothing requirements .
#Text=Naked is OK , but covered in clay will get you in trouble .
#Text=Two miles of beach on the northern side of Aquinnah , which is more sheltered than Moshup Beach around to the south .
#Text=Land Bank property for hiking , picnicking , birding .
#Text=Take a tour of the magnificent cliffs from the water .
#Text=The adventurous may want to ask about their clay bath option , using imported French bentonite clay
#Text=Stay off the cliffs and out of the clay .
#Text=Aquinnah 's only retail shops are a group of stores on Aquinnah Circle , adjacent to the Gay Head Lighthouse .
